When you become the prayer, you stop performing and start burning."Many thought I was strange, intense, too serious.

01:00:05.280 --> 01:00:14.758
But I wasn't living for them. I was under divine arrest, marked by God, set apart for something holy.

01:00:14.760 --> 01:00:18.438
The spirit had claimed my life and I surrendered to the calling.

01:00:18.439 --> 01:00:28.206
Don't expect to be understood. Expect to be used. How to live as a walking prayer: let go of normal.

01:00:28.207 --> 01:00:33.598
Intercessors often live a consecrated, misunderstood life. Yield fully.

01:00:33.599 --> 01:00:38.798
Don't ask for revival without giving God your entire schedule.

01:00:38.799 --> 01:00:44.639
Burn continuously. Stay in the posture of surrender until you embody the burden.

01:00:44.640 --> 01:00:50.078
Holy Spirit, I don't just want to pray. I want to become the prayer.

01:00:50.079 --> 01:00:57.719
Make my life an altar. Let my breath carry your groan. Possess my time, my energy, my soul.

01:00:57.720 --> 01:01:04.303
I give up normal to carry the extraordinary. Let me be a walking intercession.

01:01:04.304 --> 01:01:13.332
Let others encounter you through the fire that burns in me. Crying out for a generation you'll never meet.

01:01:13.333 --> 01:01:20.519
True intercessors sow for what they may never see. See right here, Rachel Teafatiller.

01:01:20.520 --> 01:01:32.078
Some of the people are glorious; some of these elders went on, but they were deep prayer warriors that prayed for the revival that we're about to have, and they never got to taste it.

01:01:32.079 --> 01:01:40.798
So, this is what I thought about her whenever Rachel Teafatiller and these others prayed for this revival and praying for a glorious church.

01:01:40.799 --> 01:01:49.878
Now, read that again. Read that again. I'm just trying to, you know, it's like Lucy—she never got to taste the revival.

01:01:49.880 --> 01:01:57.937
Here we are. This is it. True intercessors sow for what they may never see.

01:01:57.938 --> 01:02:02.689
I didn't just pray for the revival at hand. I prayed for the generations to come.

01:02:02.690 --> 01:02:10.719
I cried out for children I'll never meet, for preachers not yet born, for nations yet to hear.

01:02:10.720 --> 01:02:16.639
My prayers stretched into the future and seeded awakening for decades beyond me.

01:02:16.640 --> 01:02:23.290
Legacy intercession is unselfish. It's eternal. The spirit will burden you for the unseen.

01:02:23.291 --> 01:02:31.039
Many of my groans weren't even for the moment. They were for you—yes, you reading this now.

01:02:31.040 --> 01:02:36.972
I groaned for your breakthrough long before you were born. Because God doesn't see time; He sees harvest.

01:02:36.973 --> 01:02:43.488
He places future cries in present intercessors. You want to be used by God?

01:02:43.489 --> 01:02:49.118
Then pray beyond your own timeline. Your ceiling becomes their floor.

01:02:49.119 --> 01:02:53.759
Every generation of intercessors lays the foundation for the next.

01:02:53.760 --> 01:02:57.530
The groans you release now become the fire others walk in later.

01:02:57.531 --> 01:03:03.016
You may never see their revival, but your cry built the path they'll walk on.

01:03:03.017 --> 01:03:08.506
If you'll sow now, they'll reap later, and heaven will credit your faith.

01:03:08.507 --> 01:03:13.159
How to intercede for the future? Ask God for a generational burden.

01:03:13.160 --> 01:03:18.879
Let your heart stretch beyond the moment. Declare revival over tomorrow's leaders.

01:03:18.880 --> 01:03:27.679
Speak into the future by the spirit. Sacrificially give today for what only eternity will measure.

01:03:27.680 --> 01:03:32.719
Eternal God, give me a burden for the generations I'll never meet.

01:03:32.720 --> 01:03:39.038
Let me sow revival now for souls yet unborn. Let my prayers echo into the future.

01:03:39.039 --> 01:03:45.279
Mark this season with groans that outlive me. Let others run into the fire I lit.

01:03:45.280 --> 01:03:52.959
I choose to be a seed of awakening for now and forever. The joy of carrying what others can't see.

01:03:52.960 --> 01:04:00.359
There is joy in the groan. Yes, I wept. Yes, I travailed. Yes, I bled in the spirit.

01:04:00.360 --> 01:04:07.679
But hear me, there was joy—deep, unshakable joy—because I knew I was carrying something eternal.

01:04:07.680 --> 01:04:13.132
I was housing a holy burden. I was chosen by God to birth what others would celebrate.

01:04:13.133 --> 01:04:19.679
You will never be more fulfilled than when you carry God's burden with joy.

01:04:19.680 --> 01:04:22.239
Intercession isn't depression. It's divine partnership.

01:04:22.240 --> 01:04:28.308
Some think the groan is heavy and miserable. No, it is holy. It is glorious.

01:04:28.309 --> 01:04:33.519
The burden of the Lord is intense, but it is never without joy.

01:04:33.520 --> 01:04:39.199
He invites us to partner with him in the sacred act of transformation.

01:04:39.200 --> 01:04:47.358
And when you realize heaven trusts you with something, that precious joy explodes in your soul.

01:04:47.360 --> 01:04:53.989
The joy of the unseen assignment. They didn't clap for me. They didn't know my name, but heaven did.

01:04:53.990 --> 01:04:59.038
And that joy—the joy of knowing I obeyed—was stronger than any applause.

01:04:59.039 --> 01:05:06.798
I had joy unspeakable and full of glory because I was used by God to birth what others would never understand.

01:05:06.799 --> 01:05:14.132
And I wouldn't trade it for anything. How to embrace joy in the throne: recognize heaven's trust.

01:05:14.133 --> 01:05:18.131
You've been chosen to carry holy things. Celebrate obedience.

01:05:18.132 --> 01:05:23.972
Let your joy be rooted in faithfulness, not visibility. Receive the smile of God.

01:05:23.973 --> 01:05:31.519
His pleasure is your strength. Father, thank you for trusting me with a holy burden.

01:05:31.520 --> 01:05:39.919
I say yes to the groan and yes to the joy that comes with it. Let me feel your delight as I press into the unseen places.

01:05:39.920 --> 01:05:47.838
I receive the joy of obedience. Let my soul rejoice in carrying what few will ever understand.

01:05:47.839 --> 01:05:53.279
When the burden becomes your identity, you stop carrying the burden; it carries you.

01:05:53.280 --> 01:06:03.073
There comes a point in the life of an intercessor when you no longer say, 'I have a burden.'Instead, you realize the burden has you.

01:06:03.074 --> 01:06:08.958
You've become one with the groan. You're no longer dipping in and out of prayer.

01:06:08.959 --> 01:06:13.999
You are prayer. The ache of God has marked you. That's where I lived.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:21.199
I didn't visit intercession. I became intercession. You'll never be the same once the burden takes root in your spirit.

01:06:21.200 --> 01:06:28.838
Your assignment becomes your atmosphere. When I entered a city, I didn't have to ask what the burden was.

01:06:28.840 --> 01:06:34.078
I felt it. Because the intercessor carries more than prayer points. They carry atmospheres.

01:06:34.079 --> 01:06:38.558
When you're saturated in the spirit, your very presence becomes catalytic.

01:06:38.559 --> 01:06:49.892
Conviction begins before the message is preached. Glory descends before the meeting begins.

01:06:49.893 --> 01:06:56.340
Diana, I love it. The burden becomes a lens through which you see everything.

01:06:56.341 --> 01:07:01.599
When God trusts you with his groan, there is no greater honor than to be trusted with God's burden.

01:07:01.600 --> 01:07:13.199
When he lets you feel what he feels, weep where he weeps, intercede where he longs to move, it means he has found a yielded vessel.

01:07:13.200 --> 01:07:17.812
The burden isn't a weight to escape. It's an invitation into divine partnership.

01:07:17.813 --> 01:07:24.798
How to walk in your intercessory identity: stop compartmentalizing prayer.

01:07:24.799 --> 01:07:28.090
Become a walking altar. Let the burden shape your schedule.

01:07:28.091 --> 01:07:35.519
Don't resist it. Lean into it. Wear the groaning with joy. It means you've been trusted with heaven's ache.

01:07:35.520 --> 01:07:41.869
Lord, I don't want to carry a temporary burden. I want to become the intercessor you can trust.

01:07:41.870 --> 01:07:46.203
Let the weight of revival become my identity. Let your groan live inside me.

01:07:46.204 --> 01:07:52.078
Make me one with your ache. I say yes to the burden, the calling, and the cost.

01:07:52.079 --> 01:07:56.639
Praying until the glory dwells. Not just a visit, but a habitation.

01:07:56.640 --> 01:08:00.778
I wasn't praying for an event; I was crying out for a habitation.

01:08:00.779 --> 01:08:04.986
I didn't want a drop. I wanted a deluge. I didn't want God to visit.

01:08:04.987 --> 01:08:10.821
I wanted him to dwell. And for that, I groaned until the air shifted and stayed.

01:08:10.822 --> 01:08:17.758
Many pray for revival to fall. Few pray for it to rest. My cry was simple: Stay, Lord.

01:08:17.759 --> 01:08:22.839
Don't just come; remain. Only intercessors can host the glory long term.

01:08:22.840 --> 01:08:32.879
Preachers can ignite, worshippers can stir, but only intercessors can host because it takes groaning, covering, warring, and weeping to protect what God releases.

01:08:32.880 --> 01:08:39.118
Glory lingers where prayer saturates the soil. You want revival to remain in your church?

01:08:39.119 --> 01:08:45.519
Then keep the furnace of intercession burning non-stop. You become the ark that carries him.

01:08:45.520 --> 01:08:51.758
I longed to be a man that God could dwell with—not just touch occasionally, but live inside continuously.

01:08:51.759 --> 01:08:57.625
I became a walking tabernacle. I guarded his presence. I made my life his resting place.

01:08:57.626 --> 01:09:01.758
That's what sustained the glory in Finney's meetings. It wasn't structure.

01:09:01.759 --> 01:09:08.079
It was saturation. How to pray for habitation, not just visitation: guard the atmosphere.

01:09:08.080 --> 01:09:13.119
Don't let glory be treated casually. Keep praying. Did you hear that?

01:09:13.120 --> 01:09:21.838
When the Lord said to us, 'What you're about to see, do not take it for granted and let it become casual.

01:09:21.839 --> 01:09:33.197
You must honor the glory what's about to be displayed in the atmosphere of your churches and your buildings.'Don't take it as casual.

01:09:33.198 --> 01:09:44.879
Guard the atmosphere. Do not let the glory be treated casually. Don't dishonor it because you'll grieve the Holy Spirit.

01:09:44.880 --> 01:09:55.359
Every miracle—I don't care if it's a hangnail and somebody's gotten healed by something—you go, 'Well, that's not that big a deal.'Well, it was a big deal to them and it was a big deal to the Lord or he wouldn't have done it.

01:09:55.360 --> 01:10:03.417
He cares about all of it. Honor everything that's about to take place in the glorious Church.

01:10:03.418 --> 01:10:12.229
Hover over it and treat it as precious. Keep prayer central.

01:10:12.230 --> 01:10:23.759
Prayer must be the foundation, not the add-on. Ask God to dwell. Don't settle for anything less than lingering glory.

01:10:23.760 --> 01:10:30.515
Prayer must be the foundation in your church to keep the glory going, not an add-on.

01:10:30.516 --> 01:10:45.519
The glory is attached to the foundation of prayer. Ask God to dwell.

01:10:45.520 --> 01:10:53.972
Don't settle for anything less than lingering glory. I want more.

01:10:53.973 --> 01:11:02.118
It's not just going to be a one-and-done when we get there. We got it; it's here.

01:11:02.119 --> 01:11:06.158
And we won't stop praying until you make the devil a greasy spot.

01:11:06.159 --> 01:11:20.212
Smith Wigglesworth—it's like whenever you see—maybe it was Brother Hagin who said they saw this—you don't just, when you see the breakthrough, stop praying and giving God thanks and glory.

01:11:20.213 --> 01:11:29.509
You make him a greasy spot in the road like an old roadkill. You run that devil up, you back up and you hit him again, you go forward and hit him again.

01:11:29.510 --> 01:11:35.359
You keep doing it until he's a greasy spot. You make sure he's a greasy spot in your life.

01:11:35.360 --> 01:11:42.879
A lot of people give up and let go of the rope when they see the first fruits of the victory they've been believing for, and they go, 'Well, we've got it,'and let it go.

01:11:42.880 --> 01:11:57.336
Hallelujah. And you walk away. No, you keep hitting that thing even after you see the first fruits of the victory, and you back up and you hit it again and you run over and you run over again.

01:11:57.337 --> 01:12:02.639
Just like it's saying: don't settle for anything less than the lingering glory.

01:12:02.640 --> 01:12:08.170
Let it be so much so that it's taking over and you feel his presence.

01:12:08.171 --> 01:12:20.559
What is the glory? The weightiness of his presence. Whenever you can't move, you smell it. It changes you from the inside out.

01:12:20.560 --> 01:12:27.279
I've been in services like a Billy Burke meeting and the glory is so strong that you just lose track of time.

01:12:27.280 --> 01:12:34.158
Like it was Sister Billye's tent meeting that one year. People were leaving, but you could just feel the glory.

01:12:34.159 --> 01:12:40.479
I'm thinking, 'What is wrong with people?'It was five or six hours we were in that tent meeting.

01:12:40.480 --> 01:12:44.879
It was hot outside, but we lost track of time because the glory was there.

01:12:44.880 --> 01:12:48.718
And that's what the Lord said: there'd be 24-hour a day, seven-day a week services.

01:12:48.719 --> 01:12:55.186
And people will be in there going, 'It's morning already.'Everybody's healed.

01:12:55.187 --> 01:12:59.999
Everybody's in the presence of the Lord. It's six o'clock in the morning.

01:13:00.000 --> 01:13:03.127
Look at that, the sun's coming up. We've been here all night.

01:13:03.128 --> 01:13:09.543
Well, we better go home and get a little rest and get a bite to eat and then come back and do it again.

01:13:09.544 --> 01:13:17.158
I wanted to know what it was like with John Kilpatrick during Pensacola. I've always wanted to talk about that.

01:13:17.159 --> 01:13:22.959
Maybe one day he'll want to be a guest on our show to talk about the glorious outpouring in Pensacola.

01:13:22.960 --> 01:13:31.678
It's going to happen again at the Church of His Presence. We're about to taste it.

01:13:31.679 --> 01:13:39.233
A Shaking to Awaken is coming, ladies and gentlemen. I talked to somebody today on the phone and said, 'What's the tipping point?

01:13:39.234 --> 01:13:48.799
What is the domino that's about to happen?'We're about to see what we've always longed to see, but it's going to be by prayer first.

01:13:48.800 --> 01:13:57.252
And that's why we have it tonight. So, I know we've talked way too much—it's already an hour and 14 minutes—but I hope you got something out of the first half of this.

01:13:57.253 --> 01:14:08.089
I love you, baby. Thank you for being here. I appreciate it. Let's take communion and pray and be excited about what God is going to do today.

01:14:08.090 --> 01:14:15.598
I believe we're going to pray for President Trump. We're going to get through this and it's going to be wonderful.

01:14:15.599 --> 01:14:21.999
Isn't Jesus wonderful? Like Brother Hagin always said, 'Isn't Jesus wonderful?'So, ready?

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:29.519
Let's take communion. Father, we just thank you. We take communion every day here, sometimes three times a day.

01:14:29.520 --> 01:14:36.079
We make much of the blood of Jesus in this household. If you don't take communion on a regular basis, you're missing out.

01:14:36.080 --> 01:14:47.519
This is relationship, not religion. This isn't something the Catholic Church does; I look at this as relationship.

01:14:47.520 --> 01:14:53.759
Jesus Christ dwells on the inside of me. I'm wall-to-wall Holy Ghost.

01:14:53.760 --> 01:14:58.185
My wife is wall-to-wall Holy Ghost. He dwells in this house.

01:14:58.186 --> 01:15:04.718
And I take this often in remembrance of what he did for me. By his stripes, I'm healed.

01:15:04.719 --> 01:15:14.238
His blood is enough. It covers me. It makes me whole. It washes me. It defeated the devil once and for all.

01:15:14.239 --> 01:15:24.479
And I just remind him, 'Thank you, Jesus, for what you did.'Father, we take this body right now in the name of Jesus and we thank you for what you did.

01:15:24.480 --> 01:15:30.238
You whipped him, Lord. You kicked him right in the teeth and then you stepped on his head.

01:15:30.239 --> 01:15:37.299
Father, I'm so thankful for everything that you've done. You defeated Satan once and for all.

01:15:37.300 --> 01:15:43.519
And I believe, Father, that we walk in that victory and that freedom in the name of Jesus.

01:15:43.520 --> 01:15:52.399
We are the children of the Most High God and we dwell with you, seated with you in the heavenlies, far above all principalities and powers and might.

01:15:52.400 --> 01:16:03.759
We have dominion and authority over the devil and we're not going to let him run rampant in our lives. As for me and my house, we will serve the Lord.

01:16:03.760 --> 01:16:17.039
And we take this body in remembrance of what you did when you kicked his hiney and you said, 'It is finished.'I love it.

01:16:17.040 --> 01:16:29.119
He triumphed over him. The devil's defeated. And we have to continually remind him that he is.

01:16:29.120 --> 01:16:35.199
You're defeated. You're not going to run over my kids. You're not going to put sickness on my house.

01:16:35.200 --> 01:16:40.959
You're not going to put poverty on us. We have a covenant with a God who is more than enough.

01:16:40.960 --> 01:16:48.639
We call for finances in the name of Jesus. Angels of the Lord, go now and bring the finances in.

01:16:48.640 --> 01:16:58.052
Thank you, Lord, that healing flows from within. No sickness, no disease, no cancers, no diabetes, no nothing comes nigh us.

01:16:58.053 --> 01:17:05.039
Healing and wholeness and wellness belong to us. You either believe it or you don't.

01:17:05.040 --> 01:17:10.826
I'm moved by what the word says. I'm not moved by what I see or what I feel.

01:17:10.827 --> 01:17:17.839
I'm moved by what the word says. And by his stripes, I am healed. This is symbolism of it.

01:17:17.840 --> 01:17:23.359
Jesus paid the price for me to walk in victory, and we take it in the name of Jesus.

01:17:23.360 --> 01:17:30.817
Thank you, Lord, for the blood. We make much of the blood and the blood makes much of us tonight. Father, I repent of my sins.

01:17:30.818 --> 01:17:35.799
I thank you, Lord, that you are faithful and just to forgive me of my sins and cleanse me of all unrighteousness.

01:17:35.800 --> 01:17:44.559
And tonight we take the blood right now in Jesus'name. And thank you, Lord, uninterrupted and unhindered by any satanic or demonic spirit.

01:17:44.560 --> 01:17:48.358
Father, if there's anything you want to show me tonight, I thank you.

01:17:48.359 --> 01:17:55.953
I'm led by your Spirit tonight and I don't hear any demonic spirits because I'm led by you and a stranger's voice I will not follow.

01:17:55.954 --> 01:18:01.839
I cover my spiritual eyes and anything you want to show us. In Jesus'name, I plead the blood.

01:18:01.840 --> 01:18:05.678
We're not here to perform. We're here just to yield to you, Holy Spirit.

01:18:05.679 --> 01:18:09.919
So, Father, we're here to help you in any way we can. In Jesus'name, the blood of Jesus.

01:18:09.920 --> 01:18:16.930
Amen. Every time is different. Don't ever make it cookie-cutter.

01:18:16.931 --> 01:18:27.739
Thank you, Lord. At least I try not to. All right. Who wants to go tubing for a little bit?

01:18:27.740 --> 01:18:32.399
I know we kept you longer, but it's Sunday, so we preached to you and then told you it's our service.

01:18:32.400 --> 01:18:36.462
Our Sunday service—I told Dana this is Sunday service, so we preach a little longer.

01:18:36.463 --> 01:18:42.959
It's an hour and 19 minutes. I'm not a drive-thru; I'm a slow cooker.

01:18:42.960 --> 01:18:46.639
If you want McDonald's, go down the street to the secret friendlies.

01:18:46.640 --> 01:18:50.079
Go get some McDonald's from them; you ain't going to get it from me.

01:18:50.080 --> 01:19:00.680
I'm going to cook you a meal, and it's going to be prepared a little better than the McDonald's you got earlier today at your church.

01:19:00.681 --> 01:19:15.599
Just Holy Spirit, for I don't want to get in trouble. Oh Jesus.

01:19:15.600 --> 01:19:37.529
Father, we're so thankful. Holy Spirit, you are welcome in this place.

01:19:37.530 --> 01:20:20.409
Omnipotent Father of mercy and grace, thou art welcome in this place. Holy Spirit, you are welcome in this place.

01:20:20.410 --> 01:20:52.238
Omnipotent Father of mercy and grace, thou art welcome in this place.

01:20:52.239 --> 01:21:17.599
You are the God that healeth me. You are the Lord, my healer. You sent your word and healed my disease.

01:21:17.600 --> 01:21:41.678
You are the Lord, my healer. You are the God that healeth me. You are the Lord, my healer.

01:21:41.679 --> 01:22:03.198
You sent your word and you healed my disease. You are the Lord, my healer.

01:22:03.199 --> 01:22:28.718
You are the God that healeth me. You are the Lord, my healer. You sent your word and healed my disease.

01:22:28.719 --> 01:22:50.638
You are the Lord, my healer. I thank you that you are our healer tonight. I thank you, Lord, that you are our healer.

01:22:50.639 --> 01:23:08.879
I hear this—it's called in Deuteronomy 'sicknesses of a long continuance.'I am setting you free from sicknesses of a long continuance according to Deuteronomy 28.

01:23:08.880 --> 01:23:25.645
Galatians 3:13: Christ has redeemed you from the curse of the law, from sicknesses of long continuance—sicknesses that keep going on and on as a stronghold on your life.

01:23:25.646 --> 01:23:41.709
Jesus Christ paid the price for you to be delivered from sicknesses of long continuance.

01:23:41.710 --> 01:23:57.119
The Lord will make the plagues wonderful, and the plagues of thy seed even great plagues of long continuance and sore sicknesses of long continuance.

01:23:57.120 --> 01:24:19.279
Did I read that right, Lover? Deuteronomy 28:59, Galatians 3:13: Christ has redeemed me from Deuteronomy 28:59; I am no longer under that curse.

01:24:19.280 --> 01:24:28.079
And the Lord says tonight, He is the God that healeth you. He is the Lord your healer.

01:24:28.080 --> 01:24:43.919
And sicknesses of long continuance—sicknesses of long continuance are broken off of your life tonight.

01:24:43.920 --> 01:26:26.158
Take it all! He said, 'Take it all that I've given you. Take the nations.'Days of great fun have just begun.

01:26:26.159 --> 01:26:35.359
Ministry is supposed to be fun. He said ministry is supposed to be fun, for His burdens are light.

01:26:35.360 --> 01:26:45.164
Cast all your care on me, for I care for you. He takes the care out of your prayer.

01:26:45.165 --> 01:27:04.718
I'm calling you higher in your prayer time. Days of great fun have just begun for the body. He's hiding the remnant in the cleft of the rock.

01:27:04.719 --> 01:27:14.605
He told us 1 Corinthians 5:5 was the scripture for 2026, and He's cleaning the house of the Lord right now.

01:27:14.606 --> 01:27:21.999
And He said there'll be people that are preaching, they'll be there and they'll be there no more.

01:27:22.000 --> 01:27:28.718
And I'm raising up new Davids; I'm raising up new Esthers. I'm raising up new ones that will take the baton.

01:27:28.719 --> 01:27:36.559
He's putting in His dream team 2026. He's cleansing and cleaning up His bride to bring the bride to His side.

01:27:36.560 --> 01:27:46.638
And the ones, the remnant that are awakened right now, He said, 'I'm bringing you underneath that cleft of the rock.'And as the shaking goes by, it will not touch you.

01:27:46.639 --> 01:27:56.868
For you are my remnant, you're set aside. The purified bride—the ones that are already awake—you're just to intercede for the others for great shaking to awaken.

01:27:56.869 --> 01:28:11.329
Some will fall and they'll go home early; some will be removed early. I see it again; there is much shaking yet to come.

